---
import GuideLayout from '../layouts/GuideLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../lib/site';

const lastUpdated = 'May 25, 2026';
---

<GuideLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy policy for n8n.gjam.in. What data we collect, cookies, analytics, advertising, third parties, and your rights under GDPR and India DPDP Act."
  path="/privacy"
  breadcrumbs={[
    { name: 'Home', path: '/' },
    { name: 'Privacy', path: '/privacy' },
  ]}
  datePublished="2025-01-01"
>
  <p><em>Last updated: {lastUpdated}</em></p>

  <p>
    This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>{SITE.name}</strong> ("we", "us") collects, uses, and
    protects information when you visit our website. By using the site you agree to this policy.
  </p>

  <h2>Information we collect</h2>
  <h3>Information you give us</h3>
  <p>
    We do not require an account to browse or download workflows. If you email us at
    <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a>, we receive your email address and message
    content so we can reply.
  </p>

  <h3>Information collected automatically</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Standard server logs (IP address, browser type, timestamp, referrer)</li>
    <li>Google Analytics events (page views, navigation, anonymized IP)</li>
    <li>Cookies set by Google Analytics and Google AdSense (see below)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Cookies and tracking</h2>
  <p>
    We use <strong>Google Analytics</strong> (gtag.js, ID <code>{SITE.gtagId}</code>) to understand
    aggregate traffic patterns. Analytics cookies are typically valid for 24 months.
  </p>
  <p>
    We use <strong>Google AdSense</strong> (publisher ID <code>{SITE.adsensePublisherId}</code>) to
    show advertisements. Google and its partners may use cookies to serve ads based on your prior
    visits to this and other websites. You can opt out of personalized advertising at
    <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">google.com/settings/ads</a>
    or via <a href="https://www.aboutads.info" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">aboutads.info</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>How we use information</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>To operate and improve n8n.gjam.in content</li>
    <li>To answer support and editorial requests</li>
    <li>To measure aggregate site performance (no individual profiling by us)</li>
    <li>To display relevant advertising via Google AdSense</li>
    <li>To comply with legal obligations</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Third parties</h2>
  <p>The following services may receive data when you visit:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Google Analytics</strong> — aggregate site metrics</li>
    <li><strong>Google AdSense</strong> — ad serving and measurement</li>
    <li><strong>Vercel</strong> — hosting provider, processes request logs</li>
    <li><strong>Google Fonts</strong> — serves the Inter web font</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We do not sell personal information. We do not share email addresses with marketers.
  </p>

  <h2>Workflow downloads</h2>
  <p>
    Workflow files (JSON / ZIP) are served as static assets. Downloading a file does not transmit
    any additional personal data to us beyond standard server logs. Be aware that the workflow files
    you import into your own n8n instance may interact with third-party APIs (OpenAI, Apify, etc.) —
    those calls are governed by your credentials and those providers' policies, not ours.
  </p>

  <h2>Your rights</h2>
  <p>Depending on where you live, you may have rights including:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Access to personal data we hold about you</li>
    <li>Correction or deletion of that data</li>
    <li>Objection to processing or withdrawal of consent</li>
    <li>Data portability</li>
    <li>Lodging a complaint with a supervisory authority (e.g. Data Protection Board of India, EU DPA)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    To exercise any right, email <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a> with subject
    <code>Data Request</code>. We respond within 30 days.
  </p>

  <h2>Children</h2>
  <p>
    n8n.gjam.in is intended for users aged 16 and above. We do not knowingly collect data from
    children under 16. If you believe a child has provided us data, contact us for removal.
  </p>

  <h2>Data retention</h2>
  <p>
    Server logs are kept for up to 90 days. Email correspondence is retained for up to 24 months for
    support continuity. Analytics aggregates are retained per Google's defaults.
  </p>

  <h2>Security</h2>
  <p>
    The site is served over HTTPS. We do not store passwords, payment information, or sensitive
    personal data. We use reputable infrastructure providers but cannot guarantee absolute security
    of internet transmissions.
  </p>

  <h2>International transfers</h2>
  <p>
    Our service providers may process data outside India, including in the United States and EU.
    We rely on standard contractual clauses and provider compliance frameworks where applicable.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this policy. The "Last updated" date at the top reflects the latest revision.
    Material changes will be highlighted on the home page or via an in-page notice for 30 days.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about this Privacy Policy? Email
    <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a>.
  </p>
</GuideLayout>
